Simple class names should be used
Javaâ€™s import mechanism allows the use of simple class names. Therefore, using a class' fully qualified name in a file that imports the class is redundant and confusing. 
### Noncompliant
import java.util.List;
import java.sql.Timestamp;

//...

java.util.List<String> myList;  // Noncompliant
java.sql.Timestamp tStamp; // Noncompliant
### Compliant
import java.util.List;
import java.sql.Timestamp;

//...

List<String> myList;
Timestamp tStamp;
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
### Compliant
